    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - WEST COAST MAGNUM MIRRORS AND AERO MIRRORS - DESCRIPTION -
        WEST COAST MAGNUM MIRROR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>WEST COAST MAGNUM MIRROR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>A typical West Coast Magnum installation includes a heated flat mirror glass and a non-heated convex
            mirror head, each mounted separately on a "C" loop arm attached to the vehicle door. Mirror heater, CB and
            mirror motor wires run inside the "C" loop arm and connect to the cab wire harness at the lower "C" loop
            door mounting. Constant current is provided via the cab wire harness routed through the door to the mirror
            harness.
        </para>
        <para>A West Coast Magnum mirror may be serviced as a complete unit replacement, or individual components may be
            replaced as shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602802">Figure 2</hotlnk>
            and the Service Parts list below.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The lower "C" loop mounting incorporates a pre-loaded internal spring which holds the mirror in
                    one of three detent positions - full forward, driver use or full rear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Do not attempt to disassemble or otherwise tamper with the lower mounting and pivot mechanism.
                    Serious injury may result.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
